ChatGPT is a type of artificial intelligence (AI) that generates text based on prompts given to it. These prompts can range from writing a haiku to creating an imaginary news article about a leaf falling from a tree. This AI system can produce a variety of responses to a single prompt, which means it doesn't always give the same answer.

Building a system like ChatGPT is complex. It involves the use of a type of neural network called a 'Transformer', which was initially proposed in a machine translation paper. This architecture has since been utilized in various AI applications, including ChatGPT.

ChatGPT isn't something we can easily replicate. It's trained using a large amount of data from the internet, and involves numerous stages of preliminary training and fine-tuning. Simply put, it's a sophisticated AI system created through a meticulous and in-depth process.